tive =0Aaccountants to bypass a fifth year of school to make the path to a =
state =0Aaccounting license less expensive. Many states are exploring chang=
es to =0Acertified public accountant licensing laws to provide an alternati=
ve.=0A=0A=E2=80=9CToday, we can recruit the talent we need, but the shortag=
e is already =0Aimpacting our profession, as well as businesses,=E2=80=9D P=
aul Knopp, chief executive =0Aof KPMG=E2=80=99s U.S. unit, said in a Linked=
In post at the time.=0A=0AI suppose the shortage story is something like =
=E2=80=9Csure the Big Four audit firms =0Acan still hire accountants to aud=
it companies=E2=80=99 financial statements, but there =0Aaren=E2=80=99t eno=
ugh accountants to work at the companies and actually write the =0Afinancia=
l statements.=E2=80=9D I guess the auditors that KPMG lays off can go work =
for =0Athe companies, though.=0A=0A=0AWill Elon Musk divest his stock holdi=
ngs to go into public service=3F=0A=0AOne popular but frankly odd theory of=
 Elon Musk goes like this:=0A=0A * Elon Musk is the richest person in the w=
orld, based mostly on the value of =0Ahis stake in Tesla Inc. =0A * Musk wo=
uld like to diversify out of his Tesla stock. =0A * The simple way to do th=
at =E2=80=94 sell the stock and buy other stuff =E2=80=94 has some =0Aprobl=
ems. He would incur a large tax bill, for one thing. But also, selling =0AT=
esla stock would be a badsignal: Tesla=E2=80=99s stock price, in this theor=
y, reflects =0Anot just the underlying value of Tesla=E2=80=99s business bu=
t also Musk=E2=80=99s fans=E2=80=99 =0Ameme-like devotion to him personally=
, and if they knew he was dumping Tesla =0Athen the value of his stock woul=
d evaporate. =0A * Therefore, on this theory, the trick is for Musk to find=
 a way to sell his =0ATesla stock alongside some sort of distraction, so th=
at people will say not =0A=E2=80=9CMusk is dumping Tesla=E2=80=9D but rathe=
r =E2=80=9CMusk is doing some other weird cool thing, =0Aand understandably=
 he needs to sell some Tesla stock to do it,=E2=80=9D so the stock =0Astays=
 high.=0AYou saw this theory a lot when Musk was in the process of buying T=
witter Inc. =0Ain 2022 =0A<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2022-=
04-28/elon-musk-s-other-merger-worked-out=3Fcmpid=3DBBD110524_MONEYSTUFF&ut=
m_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_term=3D241105&utm_campaign=3Dm=
oneystuff>=0A: He sold a bunch of Tesla stock to pay for Twitter, diversify=
ing his portfolio =0Aa bit, but the story was not =E2=80=9CMusk is selling =
down his Tesla stake=E2=80=9D but rather =0A=E2=80=9Chere=E2=80=99s a new t=
hing Musk is doing.=E2=80=9D I don=E2=80=99t think the theory was very =0Ac=
ompelling then, because Twitter was not a very good diversifier for his =0A=
portfolio (it seems to have lost a ton of value!), but it=E2=80=99s a theor=
y. Or, =0Aearlier, Musksold a bunch of Tesla stock =0A<https://www.bloomber=
g.com/opinion/articles/2021-11-11/elon-musk-sold-some-tesla-stock-kvv74kce=
=3Fcmpid=3DBBD110524_MONEYSTUFF&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnewsletter&=
