 other anything.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So when a bank does =
a trade like this with a hedge fund, the bank is in a sense lending the hed=
ge fund an uncertain but potentially large amount of money. And regulators =
require banks to have capital against the risk that their customers won=E2=
=80=99t pay them back, which is called =E2=80=9Ccredit valuation adjustment=
=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CCVA.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foo=
tnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none =
!important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block=
;"> <span>[4]</span> </a> And so the usual situation occurs:</p><ol style=
=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"> <li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Banks are, obviously, the best people to=C2=A0<e=
m>make=C2=A0</em>these loans, which are not even loans. Banks have trading =
desks that are in the business of doing derivatives with clients, and sales=
 forces to get those clients, and big credit departments to evaluate whethe=
r the clients are good for the money. =E2=80=9CI will lend you an uncertain=
 amount of money based on how much Nvidia goes up in a year=E2=80=9D is a t=
rade that kind of has to go through a bank.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">But banks are not in a great position to=C2=A0<em>hold=C2=A0</em>th=
ese loans, because regulators impose expensive capital requirements on them=
.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So there is a market for private =
credit investors to take the risk.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He=
re=E2=80=99s an=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://links.message.bloomberg.com/u/click=
